race.comment: MORRISSETTE (16) continues to race very well. She tried hard under the 61kg last time at Pakenham and draws for every chance again. That effort was on the quick turnaround like she is on again today. Ticking lots of boxes and goes on top. MY ROCA FELLA (6) hits this fourth-up now and at the peak of his fitness following a solid run over 2040m at The Valley 23 days ago. He was an impressive winner two back at Mornington and getting back to a similar grade of race today looks a key move. Wouldn't surprise to see him raise the bar again to take this out. MARIOTA (11) is third up and ready to peak following a good effort here last time out. Should be suited by the rise in distance and is not to be discounted. BLACK PEPPERMINT (1) is another third-up who was very impressive from the back last time out. Can build on that performance.
